"Originally purchased from iTunes Japan then converted to mp3 (CBR)"

what does this mean - transcoding back to wav and converting to mp3? wouldn't this ruin the sound? sorry if i'm wrong

@tescoc

Original file was from iTunes Japan in the format of m4a. It was then converted to mp3. 

There's a difference between upconverted and converted.

Upconverted (can be called  transcoding) is the direct digital-to-digital data conversion of one encoding to another usually from the same format. For example, if someones leaks an album in mp3 format and is 256 kbps originally, someone can upconvert it to 320 kbps.

Converting = Encoding something in a different format from the original.
